# Text Analyzer / Eyal Naaman
    This project deals with analyzing long documents to identify characters and their relationships. The system allows complex queries based on graph algorithms.
    System features
    • Preprocessing: Text cleaning, and maintaining dominant words.
    • Character identification: Mapping full names and nicknames from databases (People CSV).
    • Search engine: Retrieving sentences containing specific word sequences (K-seqs).
    • Relationship analysis (Graph Theory):
    • Building a relationship graph between characters based on proximity (Window size).
    • BFS algorithm: Analyzing connectivity and finding the shortest path between entities.
    • Fixed-length paths: Detecting indirect relationships at an exact k distance.
    • Community identification: Grouping similar sentences according to a common threshold of words (Threshold).

Technical Highlights
    Search Optimization: Achieving O(1) lookup time for K-seqs using specialized Hash Maps.
    Scalability: Designed to handle large textual archives efficiently.

